values: So let's just rant for a few minutes.  HBP came out last week and everybody and their mother bought it expect me who is beyond broke.  Now all the list and half the stories have spoilers for the book in them.  Couldn't people wait a month.  The next fucking day there was stuff about it online.  Okay, I truly don't care about the spoilers, as long as they are marked clearly.  What gets me is one a couple of the list that I'm on (After Class and Glasses Reflect) there have been plot lines revealed in the subject lines.  Mostly about who dies, which I had already guessed, but I didn't want confirmation until I had read the book.  Stupid idiots.  Oh well, now I know.

<font face="Tempus Sans ITC" color="#800080">Everything has become hazy and difficult and the world seems to be beating down on me and there's nothing that I can do to stop it.  Hopefully soon I'll wake up and everything will be different, better and that aching need to hurt me,some, anything will be gone.</font>

<font color="#000000"><font face="Tempus Sans ITC" color="#0000ff">If you weren't aware, that was utter very sarcasticly.  Life has been hell lately and work today just made it worse.  Syed was off, the person replacing him wasn't there cuz her grandfather passed away.  One of my other co-workers traded shifts with someone and the replacement didn't show up.  I won't even getting into how much work I had to do.  It was crazy.</font></font>

Went out with my friends last night and for the most part it was a great time. Then my supper decided that it didn't like the alcohol I was consuming and tried to make a reappearance. I ended up going home early. It so very suck. Came home and played on the computer a bit before going to bed. Still sick today. Can't even blame it on the booze cuz I didn't drink that much.
<font color="#a8b0ea">Welcome to the world of Dead Kitten, this is my world, depressing as it is.  I'm also on here as Liljademoon, but that's my writing LJ, while this in my ranting one.</font>
